Abstract: THIS SUBPROJ INITIATED BY PROP REVISIONS 5/31/74 & 5/16/75. GRANT IS PROVIDED TO TUNISIA TO DEVELOP A MORE COMPREHENSIVE & EFFECTIVE FAMILY PLNNG PROG. IMPROVED ORGANIZATION & MGMT PROCEDURES WILL BE IMPLEMENTED BY NATL OFFICE OF POP & FP (ONPEP) INCLUDING NEW STAFFING, CLASSIFICATION & RECRUITMENT PROGS,COMMUNICATIONS & RECORD SYST,AN ACCOUNTING SYST AND COST/EFFECTIVENESS MGMT OF THE NATL PROG. USAID PROJ TEAM WILL CONSIST OF US PUBLIC HEALTH PHYSICIAN & A PUBLIC HEALTH EDUCATOR. US PHYSICIAN WILL ASSIST TUNISIAN CHIEF OF MEDICAL SERVICES DIVISION TO DEVELOP & IMPLEMENT ONPEP PLAN OF ACTION. CURRENT EXPANSION PLANS CONSISTS OF THE ASSIGNMENT OF 1 MIDWIFE FOR EACH MCH CENTER TRND TO PROVIDE FULL CONTRACEPTIVE SERVICES,MOBILE TEAMS OPERATED BY MIDWIVES WORKING OUT OF MCH CENTERS & PROVISION OF AN OB/GYN SPECIALIST IN EACH REGION TO CONSULT WITH MIDWIVES & GP'S. FACILITIES PROVIDING FULL RANGE OF CONTRACEPTIVE SERVICES & TREATMENT OF INFECTIONS WHICH PREVENT THE USE OF CONTRACEPTIVES WILL BE ESTABLISHED IN ALL LOCALITIES HAVING 15,000 OR MORE INHABITANTS WITHIN ARADIUS OF 10 MI. 80% OF ALL RURAL CONTRACEPTIVE DISPENSARIES WILL BE REGULARLY VISITED BY MOBILE MEDICAL TEAMS. MCH CENTERS WILL INSTITUTE PRIVATE FP COUNSELING. ALSO STANDARDS OF HYGIENE WILL BE PROMULGATED FOR MCH CENTERS WITH INSPECTIONS BY MINIS OF HEALTH OR ONPEP PERSONNEL. US HEALTH EDUCATOR WILL SERVE AS COUNTERPART TO CHIEF OF COMMUNICATIONS & EDUC DIV. DIV WILL BE EXPANDED, ADDING 2 NEW HLTH EDUCATORS AT THE NATL LEVEL & 20 AT THE REGIONAL LEVEL. US MASTER'S DEGREE TRNG WILL BE AVAILABLE FOR 25 PARTICIPANTS IN THE HLTH EDUC FIELD & 1 IN FP STATISTICS & EVALUATION. SHORT-TERM TRNG IN SEX EDUC COUNSELING & COMMUNICATIONS IS ALSO PLNND. THROUGH A SPECIAL GRANT(FROM SALE OF SOY BEAN OIL) AID WILL SUPPOR ON-GOING IDA CONSTRUCTION PROJ. 3 MATERNITY HOSPITALS & 29 MCH/FP CENTERS WILL BE BUILT. 1 PARAMEDICAL TRNG FACILITY WILL BE ENLARGED & EXISTING MCH CENTERS REMODELED. FULL-TIME TUNISIAN ARCHITECT WILL SUPERVISE CONSTRUCTION. USAID WILL ALSO FINANCE CONTRACEPTIVES,MEDICINES,MEDICAL EQUIP & VEHICLES. HOST-COUNTRY PROVIDES PERSONNEL & LONG-TERM MAINTENANCE.

Abstract: INTER-AMERICAN INSTITUTE OF AGRICULTURAL SCIENCE (IICA) DEVELOPS CAPACITY TO REVIEW, EVALUATE AND PUBLISH COMPLETED RESEARCH AND PUBLISH USEFUL FINDINGS, AND PERFORM THE SAME OPERATION WITH ONGOING AND FUTURE PROJECTS. ADDITIONALLY, IICA WILL URGE EXPERIMENT STATIONS AND RESEARCH CENTERS TO ADOPT MODERN TECHNIQUES AND PROCEDURES. A REGION-WIDE PLAN WILL BE DEVELOPED FOR COORDINATED RESEARCH AND PUBLICATION OF FINDINGS. CONFERENCES AMONG RESEARCHERS AND RESEARCH ADMINISTRATORS WILL PROVIDE A FORUM FOR PROGRAM COORDINATION AND EXCHANGE OF INFORMATION. ENCOURAGES SYSTEMS APPROACH TOREGIONAL AGRICULTURAL DEVELOPEMENT. DESIGNS INTEGRATED RESEARCH PROGRAMS AT REGIONAL LEVEL. PROVIDES TECHNICAL SERVICE.

Abstract: 1960 AID LOAN TO FINANCE WATER STORAGE, TRANSMISSION FACILITIES IS BEHIND SCHEDULE. CURRENT LOAN FINANCES COMPLETION OF REMAINING WORKS REQUIRED TO IRRIGATE SECTORS WHICH OFFER OPTIMUM COMBINATION OF HIGHEST RETURN ON INCREMENTAL INVESTMENT AND EARLY COMPLETION. LOAN ALSO FINANCES SERVICES OF US AGRICULTURAL MANAGEMENT FIRM TO ACCELERATE ECONOMIC PAY-OFF, PERFORM MARKET STUDIES, TRAIN MOROCCAN STAFF. PROJECT WORKS CONSIST OF CONSTRUCTION OF MAIN CANALS, DRAINAGE WORKS, LAND PREPARATION IN SOME AREAS AND ESTABLISHMENT OF FARMER SUPPORT CENTERS, COMMUNITY FACILITIES.

Abstract: THIS STUDY WAS UNDERTAKEN TO DETERMINE THE OPTIMUM LEVEL OF LYSINE WHICH MUST BE ADDED TO WHITE FLOUR TO MAKE IT EFFECTIVE AS THE MAIN OR ONLY SOURCE OF PROTEIN IN THE DIETS OF GROWING INFANTS AND PRESCHOOL CHILDREN. IN EACH OF THE FOUR RECOVERING MALNOURISHED INFANTS STUDIED FOR THEIR ISONITROGENOUS AND ISOCALORIC LEVELS, THE PERFORMANCE OF UNSUPPLEMENTED FLOUR WAS COMPARED WITH CASEIN AND WITH THE SAME FLOUR ENRICHED WITH LYSINE AT THREE DIFFERENT LEVELS. ALL DIETS WERE WELL ACCEPTED AND TOLERATED. THE PERCENTAGE ABSORPTION OF NITROGEN WAS REMARKABLY HIGH FOR THE LYSINE-ADDED DIETS, WITH VALUES ALMOST IDENTICAL TO CASEIN DIETS. AS FOR NITROGEN RETENTION, THE RESULTS FOR UNENRICHED WHEAT WERE ALMOST INVARIABLY LOWER THAN THOSE OF THE PRECEDING AND FOLLOWING CASEIN-DIET PERIODS. THE RESULTS SHOW THAT LYSINE HAS A NOTABLE SUPPLEMENTARY EFFECT IN CHILDREN RECEIVING WHEAT AS THE MAIN SOURCE OF PROTEIN.  THE EQUIVALENT OF 0.11% LYSINE ENRICHMENT OF ORDINARY WHEAT FLOUR PRODUCED STRIKING IMPROVEMENTS IN WEIGHT GAIN AND IN APPARENT NITROGEN RETENTION, WHILE MAINTAINING NORMAL SERUM PROTEIN AND PLASMA AMINO ACID LEVELS. FURTHER ENRICHMENT TO THE EQUIVALENT OF 0.18% LYSINE IS APPARENTLY RESULTING IN FURTHER IMPROVEMENT, BUT ADDITIONAL OBSERVATIONS ARE UNDER WAY TO CONFIRM THIS PRELIMINARY FINDING.

Abstract: THIS PAPER DESCRIBES STUDIES CONDUCTED TO EVALUATE AN INDIRECT HEMAGGLUTINATION TEST FOR MALARIA. ANTIGEN WAS PREPARED FROM MATURE SCHIZONTS OF PLASMODIUM KNOWLESI (ONE OF THE FOUR HUMAN MALARIA PARASITE SPECIES) HARVESTED FROM RHESUS MONKEY BLOOD. THE PLASMODIA WERE FREED FROM RED BLOOD CELLS WITH DISTILLED WATER AND THEN DISRUPTED IN A FRENCH PRESSURE CELL. A 2% NAC1 EXTRACT OF THE DISRUPTED PLASMODIA WAS USED TO SENSITIZE GROUP 0 TANNED ERYTHROCYTES FROM HUMAN BLOOD. THE IHA TEST DETECTED ANTIBODY TITERS OF 1: 16 OR GREATER IN 98% OF SLIDE-PROVED CASES OF MALARIA, AND IN LESS THAN 1% OF SERUM FROM PERSONS WITHOUT A HISTORY OF MALARIA. PROBLEMS IN THIS TECHNIQUE INCLUDED HARVESTING THE CORRECT STAGE OF PLASMODIA FOR ANTIGEN, USING THE FRENCH PRESSURE CELL, AND STORING THE LABILE DISRUPTED PREPARATION. THESE VARIABLES HAVE BEEN CONTROLLED IN A TEST THAT CAN DETECT ANTIBODY AGAINST A SPECTRUM OF PLASMODIA THAT INFECT PRIMATES, WITH A MINIMUM EXPENDITURE OF ANTIGEN. EVALUATION OF THE TECHNIQUE FOR FIELD STUDIES INDICATES THAT PLASMA ELUTED FROM FILTER PAPER RECTANGLES ARE SUITABLE FOR TITRATION. THIS METHOD REQUIRES FURTHER STUDY. SEROEPIDEMIOLOGICAL STUDIES WITH 10,956 SERA OF MILITARY RECRUITS FROM FOUR COUNTRIES IN THE WESTERN HEMISPHERE SUGGEST THAT THE IHA TEST MAY BE USEFUL IN THE STUDY OF EPIDEMIOLOGY OF MALARIA. DISCREPANCIES BETWEEN THE PREVALENCE OF MALARIA ESTIMATED BY SEROLOGICAL METHODS AND BY ACTIVE AND PASSIVE SURVEILLANCE REQUIRE FURTHER STUDY AND EVALUATION.

Abstract: AN INDIRECT HEMAGGLUTINATION (IHA) TEST FOR MALARIA WAS EVALUATED. ANTIGEN WAS PREPARED FROM MATURE SCHIZONTS OF PLASMODIUM KNOWLESI HARVESTED FROM THE BLOOD OF THE RHESUS MONKEY. THE PLASMODIA WERE FREED FROM RED BLOOD CELLS WITH DISTILLED WATER AND THEN DISRUPTED IN A FRENCH PRESSURE CELL. A 2% NAC1 EXTRACT OF THE DISRUPTED PLASMODIA WAS USED TO SENSITIZE HUMAN, GROUP 0 TANNED ERYTHROCYTES. THIS IHA TEST DETECTED ANTIBODY TITERS OF 1: 16 OR GREATER IN 98% OF SLIDE-PROVED CASES OF MALARIA IN LESS THAN 1% OF SERUM FROM PERSONS WITHOUT A HISTORY OF MALARIA. THE MAJOR PROBLEMS IN THIS TECHNIQUE INCLUDED HARVESTING THE CORRECT STAGE OF PLASMODIA FOR ANTIGEN, USING THE FRENCH PRESSURE CELL, AND STORING THE LABILE DISRUPTED PREPARATION. CONTROL OF THESE VARIABLES HAS MADE POSSIBLE A TEST THAT CAN DETECT ANTIBODY AGAINST A SPECTRUM OF PLASMODIA THAT INFECT PRIMATES, WITH A MINIMUM EXPENDITURE OF ANTIGEN.
Personal Author: Rogers, W. A.|Fried, J. A.|Kagan, Irving G.

Document Title: Serologic diagnosis of malaria; annual report, 1968
Category: Thesaurus~Thesaurus Collection~Health~Diseases~Parasitic diseases~Malaria|Notation~Notation Collection~K~K03~K03.C~K03.CL|Thesaurus~Thesaurus Collection~Health~Diseases~Water related diseases~Malaria|Notation~Notation Collection~K~K03~K03.N~K03.NG|Notation~Notation Collection~K~K34~K34.4~K34.42|Document Type~Document Type Collection~Program Documents (all)~Annual Report|Thesaurus~Thesaurus Collection~Health~Health care~Disease detection~Serodiagnosis

Abstract: THE PURPOSE OF THIS PROJECT IS TO DEVELOP SIMPLE, RAPID, ACCURATE METHODS FOR THE SEROLOGIC DIAGNOSIS OF MALARIA. EFFORTS HAVE BEEN CONCENTRATED ON EVALUATING AND STANDARDIZING THE INDIRECT HEMAGGLUTINATION TECHNIQUE (IHA) FOR THE DETECTION OF MALARIA ANTIBODY FOR EPIDEMIOLOGICAL STUDIES, AND THE INDIRECT FLUORESCENT ANTIBODY TEST (IFA) FOR DIAGNOSTIC AND SEROLOGIC SPECIATION OF MALARIA. WITH RESPECT TO THE IHA TEST, THE INITIAL GOALS OF THE PROGRAM HAVE BEEN ACHIEVED, IN THAT THE TEST HAS BEEN STANDARDIZED AND SHOWN TO BE A REPRODUCTIBLE, SENSITIVE, AND SPECIFIC TECHNIQUE FOR THE DIAGNOSIS OF MALARIA. FILTER-PAPER COLLECTION OF BLOOD HAS BEEN DESIGNED AND EVALUATED, AND HAS BEEN USED FOR THE PAST YEAR WITH EXCELLENT RESULTS. BLOOD ON FILTER PAPER, COLLECTED IN NEPAL, PANAMA, ETHIOPIA, AND OTHER PARTS OF THE WORLD, HAS ARRIVED AT THE U.S.P.H.S. CENTER FOR DISEASE CONTROL IN ATLANTA IN EXCELLENT CONDITION FOR TITRATION. APPLICATION OF THE IHA TEST FOR SEROEPIDEMIOLOGIC PURPOSES HAS BEEN INITIATED. STUDIES HAVE BEEN DESIGNED TO ANSWER SUCH QUESTION AS WHETHER THE IHA PROCEDURE FOR MEASURING MALARIAL ANTIBODY IN A POPULATION CORRELATED WITH PARASITOLOGIC METHODS OF MALARIA SURVEILLANCE, WHAT THE DURATION OF THE HEMAGGLUTINATION ANTIBODY RESPONSE IS, WHETHER THE IHA TEST CAN BE USED TO DELINEATE THE TRANSMISSION ZONE OF MALARIA, AND WHETHER IT CAN BE USED TO DETECT FOCAL OUTBREAKS OF MALARIA IN ENDEMIC AREAS. WITH RESPECT TO THE IFA STUDIES, A THICK SMEAR ANTIGEN HAS BEEN EMPLOYED AND EXTENSIVELY EVALUATED. THE IFA TEST NOW AVAILABLE IS 95% SENSITIVE AND ABOUT 99% SPECIFIC ON A DAY-TO-DAY BASIS, USING FOUR-FOLD DILUTIONS. USING HOMOLOGOUS ANTIGEN FOR HUMAN MALARIA, THE IFA TEST WILL CORRECTLY SPECIATE MALARIA ANTIBODY 84% OF THE TIME, AND WILL GIVE FALSE POSITIVES IN LESS THAN 5% OF THE SAMPLES TESTED.

Abstract: THIS REPORT INCLUDES THE CONFERENCE'S OPENING ADDRESSES, COUNTRY NUTRITION REPORTS, THEMATIC PRESENTATIONS, COMMITTEE REPORTS, AND THE CLOSING CEREMONIES.
